The paper deals with a problem of managing multiple mobile resources (servers) in a Euclidean space, which involves optimization and decision-making. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.DS and cs.GT seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper involves designing algorithms and analyzing their competitiveness, which are core topics in these areas. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty and optimization, which are common themes in AI, control systems, and machine learning.
